metadata.name: API::ScenariosController .search logged in retrieves expected scenario data with code_objects, labels, not_labels

children.name: issue
children.source:
def issue(login, description: nil, encode: true)
      api_key = DAO::ApiKey.new.tap do |api_key|
        api_key.login = login
        api_key.description = description if description.present?
        api_key.save
      end

      return encode(api_key) if encode

      api_key
    end

children.name: encode
authenticate
children.source:
def authenticate(api_key)
      login, key = decode(api_key)
      result = DAO::ApiKey.where(login: login).match(key)

      if result.present?
        touch(result)
        User::Show.new(result.user)
      else
        nil
      end
    end

children.name: touch
children.source:
def touch(api_key)
      if api_key.last_used.nil? || api_key.last_used > 15.minutes.ago
        api_key.last_used = Time.now
        api_key.save_changes
      end

      api_key
    end

children.name: search_api
children.source:
def search_api(params)
      matching_scenarios = base_dataset_filter.select(Sequel.as(:id, :scenario_id))
      search_params = %w[mapsets code_objects labels not_labels not_code_objects]
      params.each do |key, value|
        if search_params.include?(key) && value.present?
          matching_scenarios = matching_scenarios.public_send("filter_by_#{key}", value)
        end
      end

      query = Sequel::Model.db[:matching_scenarios]
        .with(:matching_scenarios, matching_scenarios)
        .join(:scenarios, [[Sequel[:scenarios][:id], Sequel[:matching_scenarios][:scenario_id]]])
        .select(:mapset_id, :uuid)
        .group_by(:mapset_id, :uuid, :labels)

      # If labels were requested, calculate the intersection between labels requested and
      # labels present on the scenario. Otherwise, null.
      if params[:labels].present?
        query = query.select_append(
          Sequel.as(
            Sequel.lit('ARRAY(SELECT UNNEST(labels) INTERSECT SELECT UNNEST(?))', Sequel.pg_array(params[:labels])),
            :labels
          )
        )
      else
        query = query.select_append(Sequel.as(nil, :labels))
      end

      # Don't bother joining objects that aren't in the requested code_objects. Otherwise,
      # we won't return the intersection between the code objects requested and the code
      # objects in the scenario.
      if params[:code_objects].present?
        code_object_join_conditions = [
          Sequel.lit('scenario_code_objects.scenario_id = matching_scenarios.scenario_id'),
          Sequel.expr { { object_name: params[:code_objects] } }
        ]

        query = query.select_append(
          Sequel.as(
            Sequel.lit('array_agg(object_name)'),
            :object_names
          )
        ).inner_join(:scenario_code_objects, code_object_join_conditions.reduce(&:&))
      end

      query = Sequel::Model.db[:scenarios]
                .join(query.as(:subquery), [[Sequel[:scenarios][:uuid], Sequel[:subquery][:uuid]]])
                .select(Sequel.lit('subquery.*'), :metadata)
      query.map do |row|
        ApiItem.new(row[:mapset_id], row[:uuid], row[:object_names] || [], row[:metadata], row[:labels] || [])
      end
    end

children.name: filter
children.source:
def filter(dataset, table_name: nil)
    # Don't hide anything from an admin
    # This should be replaced at some point with a proper impersonation system
    return dataset if user&.admin?

    DAO::PublicResource.coerce(dataset)
                       .scope(user, scope: scope)
  end

children.name: coerce
children.comment: # Coerce a dataset to a type that is safe to invoke scope.
children.source:
def self.coerce(dataset)
      if dataset.is_a?(PublicResource)
        dataset
      else
        UnscopableResource.new(dataset)
      end
    end

children.name: scope
children.source:
def scope(user, scope: Search::SCOPE_MEMBERSHIP)
      if user
        user = DAO::User[user.id]
      else
        raise Exceptions::Forbidden if scope == Search::SCOPE_MEMBERSHIP
      end

      case scope
      when Search::SCOPE_MEMBERSHIP
        dataset.scope_membership(user)
      when Search::SCOPE_PUBLIC
        dataset.scope_public
      when Search::SCOPE_LISTABLE
        dataset.scope_listable(user)
      when Search::SCOPE_FINDABLE
        dataset.scope_findable(user)
      end
    end

children.name: build_where_clause
children.source:
def build_where_clause(dataset, clauses)
        dataset = dataset.where(clauses.shift)
        clauses.each do |clause|
          dataset = dataset.or(clause)
        end
        dataset
      end

children.name: index
children.source:
def index
      raise Exceptions::InvalidArguments.new('search', 'mapsets are required') unless params[:mapsets].present?

      validate_params_intersection('labels', 'not_labels')
      validate_params_intersection('code_objects', 'not_code_objects')

      scenarios = search_scope(Scenario, scope: Search::SCOPE_MEMBERSHIP).search_api(params)
      render json: scenarios, status: :ok
    end

sql_query.sql: SELECT subquery.*, "metadata" FROM "scenarios" INNER JOIN (WITH "matching_scenarios" AS (SELECT "id" AS "scenario_id" FROM "scenarios" WHERE ((("scenarios"."org_id" IN (SELECT "orgs"."id" FROM "orgs" INNER JOIN "users_orgs" ON ("users_orgs"."org_id" = "orgs"."id") WHERE (("users_orgs"."user_id" = 1000001) AND ("orgs"."id" IS NOT NULL)))) OR ("scenarios"."mapset_id" IN (SELECT "mapsets"."id" FROM "mapsets" WHERE (("mapsets"."app_id" IN (SELECT "apps"."id" FROM "apps" WHERE (("apps"."org_id" IN (SELECT "orgs"."id" FROM "orgs" INNER JOIN "users_orgs" ON ("users_orgs"."org_id" = "orgs"."id") WHERE (("users_orgs"."user_id" = 1000001) AND ("orgs"."id" IS NOT NULL)))) AND ("apps"."id" IS NOT NULL)))) AND ("mapsets"."id" IS NOT NULL))))) AND (EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "scenario_code_objects" WHERE (("scenario_id" = "scenarios"."id") AND ("object_name" IN ('models/Session.delete', 'models/User.find', 'controllers/SessionsController'))) LIMIT 1)) AND (labels && ARRAY['positive']) AND ("mapset_id" IN ('100001')) AND (NOT(labels && ARRAY['negative'])))) SELECT "mapset_id", "uuid", ARRAY(SELECT UNNEST(labels) INTERSECT SELECT UNNEST(ARRAY['positive'])) AS "labels", array_agg(object_name) AS "object_names" FROM "matching_scenarios" INNER JOIN "scenarios" ON ("scenarios"."id" = "matching_scenarios"."scenario_id") INNER JOIN "scenario_code_objects" ON (scenario_code_objects.scenario_id = matching_scenarios.scenario_id AND ("object_name" IN ('models/Session.delete', 'models/User.find', 'controllers/SessionsController'))) GROUP BY "mapset_id", "uuid", "labels") AS "subquery" ON ("scenarios"."uuid" = "subquery"."uuid")
